Gold Gains to Record as Failure to Raise Debt Limit Spurs Default Concern

-- B y   P h o e b e   S e d g m a n
-- 
2011-07-24T22:23:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/gold-gains-to-record-as-failure-to-raise-debt-limit-spurs-default-concern.html
Gold for August delivery surged as
much as 0.9 percent, extending its rally to a record $1,616.50
an ounce in  New York . The metal traded at $1,615 an ounce at
8:19 a.m. in  Melbourne .    Republicans challenged a presidential veto threat by
preparing for a short-term extension of the U.S. debt limit,
hardening partisan differences in the face of warnings that a
stalemate risks roiling financial markets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
